",["$r","p",null,{"children":["To prepare a component for assertions, wrap the code rendering it and performing updates inside an ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"await act()"}]," call. This makes your test run closer to how React works in the browser."]}],"
",["$r","Note",null,{"children":["$r","p",null,{"children":["You might find using ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"act()"}]," directly a bit too verbose. To avoid some of the boilerplate, you could use a library like ",["$r","a",null,{"href":"https://testing-library.com/docs/react-testing-library/intro","target":"_blank","rel":"nofollow noopener noreferrer","children":"React Testing Library"}],", whose helpers are wrapped with ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"act()"}],"."]}]}],"
