",["$r","ul",null,{"children":["
",["$r","li",null,{"children":[["$r","code",null,{"children":"async actFn"}],": An async function wrapping renders or interactions for components being tested. Any updates triggered within the ",["$r","code",null,{"children":"actFn"}],", are added to an internal act queue, which are then flushed together to process and apply any changes to the DOM. Since it is async, React will also run any code that crosses an async boundary, and flush any updates scheduled."]}],"
"]}],"
